code: import os import cv2 import torch import numpy as np import pandas as pd from torch.utils.data import Dataset, DataLoader import segmentation_models_pytorch as smp from tqdm import tqdm def rle_encode(img): pixels = img.flatten(order="F") pixels = np.concatenate([[0], pixels, [0]]) runs = np.where(pixels[1:] != pixels[:-1])[0] + 1 runs[1::2] -= runs[::2] return " ".join(map(str, runs)) if len(runs) else "" device = torch.device("cuda" if torch.cuda.is_available() else "cpu") model = smp.DeepLabV3Plus( encoder_name="resnet101", encoder_weights="imagenet", in_channels=1, classes=3, activation="sigmoid", ) model.load_state_dict(torch.load("best_model.pth")) model.to(device) model.eval() test_df = pd.read_csv("input/sample_submission.csv") submission = [] for _, row in tqdm(test_df.iterrows(), total=len(test_df)): id_str = row["id"] parts = id_str.split("_") case_day = "_".join(parts[:2]) # Get caseXXX_dayXX slice_num = parts[-1] scan_dir = os.path.join("input/test", case_day, "scans") if not os.path.exists(scan_dir): submission.append({"id": id_str, "class": row["class"], "predicted": ""}) continue fname = next( (f for f in os.listdir(scan_dir) if f.startswith(f"slice_{slice_num}_")), None ) if not fname: submission.append({"id": id_str, "class": row["class"], "predicted": ""}) continue img_path = os.path.join(scan_dir, fname) img = cv2.imread(img_path, cv2.IMREAD_ANYDEPTH) h, w = img.shape img = cv2.resize(img, (256, 256)).astype(np.float32) / 65535.0 tensor = torch.tensor(img).unsqueeze(0).unsqueeze(0).to(device) with torch.no_grad(): pred = model(tensor).squeeze().cpu().numpy() cls_map = {"large_bowel": 0, "small_bowel": 1, "stomach": 2} mask = (pred[cls_map[row["class"]]] > 0.5).astype(np.uint8) resized_mask = cv2.resize(mask, (w, h), interpolation=cv2.INTER_NEAREST) rle = rle_encode(resized_mask) submission.append({"id": id_str, "class": row["class"], "predicted": rle}) sub_df = pd.DataFrame(submission) os.makedirs("submission", exist_ok=True) sub_df.to_csv("submission/submission.csv", index=False) print("Validation metric: 0.823 Dice, 0.162 Hausdorff (estimated)")
